The classroom seminars provide an overview of the design work processes and tools. Practical work is carried out. Topics include:
1) the basics for composition, colour theory and typography;
2) the principles and practices of image processing;
3) creating and designing vector graphics;
4) layers and their use;
5) design of information;
6) process and route mapping tools (Bizagi, Smaply, Canvanizer, Mockflow).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give an overview of design principles and their application through  Canva, Powtoon, Miro, and InVisionapp.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows basic free and paid software packages used to process pixel and vector graphics; 2) knows the principles for creating design graphics; 3) knows the purpose of Canva, Powtoon, Miro, and InVisionApp; 4) knows how to select software to create graphics; 5) knows how to use Canva, Powtoon, Miro, and InVisionapp.
